headline: Machine Learning and Computer Vision engineer | Software developer | Computational Color and Spectral Imaging (Erasmus mundus masters) graduate and scholarship winner | Paris based
creator: False
school_1: Norwegian University of Science and Technology (NTNU)
bio:
Machine Learning/Computer Vision engineer with 3 years of experience. Some of the completed research objectives include: implementing from scratch aircraft detection, tracking and localisation system; improving accuracy (>95%) and inference time (-20%) of a license plate recognition pipeline; developing a controlled generative network for grayscale to colourful images transformation. This was complemented by production-oriented software engineering for both edge devices (C++) and cloud environments (Python). I deepened my knowledge in Image Processing and 3D Computer Vision during my international masters degree, while at the same time got familiar with color science and hyper-spectral imaging.
I also have an experience working with Natural Language Processing tasks, such as Named Entity Recognition for biomedical corpuses and Propaganda detection in news outlets.

Experienced Software Engineer in Test. 

I have extensive knowledge in manual testing and automated testing with sufficient knowledge in designing test cases, test plans, test scenarios, test data & test strategies.

As a test engineer majority of my testing has been centered on functional testing, UI testing, API testing, unit testing, integration testing, regression testing. 

My skills also includes hard knowledge of the Java, Python, Selenium, Selenide, PyTest, Allure, Junit, TestNG, Postman, Jira, Confluence.

I am a responsible, goal-oriented, and organized professional who is ready to take responsibility for the quality of software. I strive for continuous development and improvement of my skills. I am always open to new technologies and work methods to stay up-to-date with the latest trends in testing.
